{"lemma":"تِرْبِ","slug":"تِرْبِ","root":"ت.ر.ب","root_slug":"ت-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3822","n3823","n3827","n3828","n3829","n3830"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be dusty, to be covered with dust, to have earth on oneself"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be so poor as to cleave to the dust","tags":["idiomatic"],"examples":[{"text":"أَمَّا مُعَاوِيَةُ فَرَجُلٌ تَرِبَ لَا مَالَ لَهُ","english":"So far as Muʿāwiya is concerned, he is a poor man without any property."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to decrease (of one's wealth)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put earth on, to sprinkle with dust"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover with dust or earth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coeval, contemporary; peer; fellow"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dusty; soiled"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cleaving to the dust by reason of want, destitute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of تُرْبَة (turba)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tu.rab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3822","headword_ar":"تَرِبَ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarabN","text_ar":"تَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became dusted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dusty; dust lighted upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a place, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had much dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth; abounded with dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, in his hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-  Also, (T, S, M, &c.,) inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he clave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, by reason of poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became so poor that he clave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became poor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he clave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he suffered loss, and became poor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he clave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) inf. n. as above, (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"matorabapN","text_ar":"مَتْرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"matorabN","text_ar":"مَتْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or both of these: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his wealth became little;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Atrb","text_ar":"اترب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tr~b","text_ar":"ترّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Atrb","text_ar":"اترب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (T, S, M,) or signifies also, (A, K,) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariba","text_ar":"تَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tr~b","text_ar":"ترّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his wealth became much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it was like the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the more known meaning of the verb; (M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became rich;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he became possessed of wealth equal in quantity to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) accord. to Abu-l-'Abbás, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatoriybN","text_ar":"تَتْرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much wealth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little wealth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariba baEoda maA A^atoraba","text_ar":"تَرِبَ بَعْدَ مَا اَتْرَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became poor after he had been rich."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taribato yadaAka","text_ar":"تَرِبَتْ يَدَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, A, Msb, in the M and K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadaAhu","text_ar":"يَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) a form of imprecation, (S, Msb,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thine arms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy hands, cleave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, by reason of poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is implied in the T: or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may thy hands have in them dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 275:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou not obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attain, good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou be unsuccessful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fail of attaining thy desire, and suffer loss:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) occurring in a trad., and as some relate, (A'Obeyd, T,) not meant as an imprecation; (A'Obeyd, T, Msb;) being a phrase current with the Arabs, who use it without desiring its fulfilment; (A'Obeyd, T;) but meant to incite, or instigate: (Msb:) some say that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may thy hands become rich;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is a mistake: (A'Obeyd, T:) and it is said to mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~`hi dar~uka","text_ar":"لِلّٰهِ دَرُّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr","text_ar":"در"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and some say that it is literally an imprecation: but the first assertion is the most worthy of respect, (that it is not meant as an imprecation,) and is corroborated by the saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoEimo SabaAHFA taribato yadaAka","text_ar":"اِنْعِمْ صَبَاحًا تَرِبَتْ يَدَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mayest thou have a pleasant morning: may thine arms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy hands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taribato jabiynuhu","text_ar":"تَرِبَتْ جَبِينُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May his forehead"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbyn","text_ar":"جبين"},{"kind":"text","text":"here means, as it does in some other instances,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] was said by Mohammad in reproving a man, and is said to mean a prayer that the man might be frequent in prostrating himself in prayer. (TA from a trad.) And he said to one of his companions,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taribato naHoruka","text_ar":"تَرِبَتْ نَحْرُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May the uppermost part of thy breast cleave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and the man was [afterwards] slain a martyr: therefore this is to be understood in its obvious sense. (TA.)       -A2-  See also 4, in four places."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","T","Msb","A"]},{"entry_id":"n3823","headword_ar":"ترّب","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatoriybN","text_ar":"تَتْرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in three places:       -A2-  and see also 4, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3827","headword_ar":"تَرْبٌ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3828","headword_ar":"تُرْبٌ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3829","headword_ar":"تِرْبٌ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One born at the same time with thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a coëtanean; a contemporary in birth; an equal in age: an equal; a match; a fellow; a peer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compeer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lidapN","text_ar":"لِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, M, A, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, A, K:) applied to a male and to a female; (TA;) but mostly to a female; (M;) or, accord. to an opinion confirmed by [most of] the leading lexicologists, only to a female; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaronN","text_ar":"قَرْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a male; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lidapN","text_ar":"لِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a male and a female: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoraAbN","text_ar":"اَتْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, A.) [The following exs. are given.] You say, [applying it to a female,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi tirobu h`*ihi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ تِرْبُ هٰذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa tirobuhaA","text_ar":"هِىَ تِرْبُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa tirobiY","text_ar":"هِىَ تِرْبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and [applying it to females and males,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA tirobaAni","text_ar":"هُمَا تِرْبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hun~a A^atoraAbN","text_ar":"هُنَّ اَتْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^atoraAbN","text_ar":"هُمْ اَتْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) Accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurubFA A^atorabFA","text_ar":"عُرُبًا اَتْرَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lvi. 36], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Showing love to their husbands;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal, unto them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is a good rendering, as there is no begetting or bearing of children, [or rather as the latter word does not apply to females born or generated,] in that case. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","A","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3830","headword_ar":"تَرِبٌ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a place, (M, TA,) and to soil, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abounding with dust; dusty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA:) and to food, (T,) or flesh-meat, (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with dust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) You say also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN tarobaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ تَرْبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land in which are dust and moist earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN taribapN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ تَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taribN","text_ar":"تَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wind that carries with it dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brings dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that drives along the dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] thus used it is a possessive epithet. (M.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cleaving to the dust by reason of want; having nothing between him and the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaving to the dust by reason of poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor, as though cleaving to the dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and [simply,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"needy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutoribN","text_ar":"مُتْرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","T","A","S","IAar","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}